"$:/plugins/telmiger/Tix/readme": {
    "created": "20220319164308353",
    "creator": "Thomas Elmiger",
    "text": "!! A Novel Tiddler Experience

There are four to five main parts or segments in your tiddler now. Four in Tix and an additional one in the separate Btx plugin: 

; tiddler-top
: the space <q>above</q> the tiddler is a good place for title/id and one or several buttons from the tiddler toolbar
; tiddler-header
: you see tags here and some toolbar buttons again – but anything could appear here
; tiddler-body
: nothing special, just tiddler content
; tiddler-footer
: tiddler meta data like dates and author info could be shown here – but again you can tag anything to show it in this part of the tiddler
; tiddler-bottom
: the space <q>below</q> the tiddler is used for buttons one might want to use //after// seeing through the tiddler – it comes with the Btx plugin


!!! Toolbar Buttons
There are toolbars everywhere. The ones in the top and header parts sort their buttons as TiddlyWiki does per default.

The toolbars in the footer and at the bottom sort their buttons in the order of activation.


!!! Tiddler Content Items

You can populate the tiddler parts using ''tags'' – all but the body. The elements shown in the following tags are just a good starting point. Click the tag pills for access to items, rearrange them via drag and drop in the list that pops up.

<<tag $:/tags/TiddlerTop>>
<<tag $:/tags/TiddlerHeader>>
<<tag $:/tags/TiddlerFooter>>
<<tag $:/tags/TiddlerBottom>>

Don’t forget to visit the configuration tab and choose your buttons and style options there. And install Lox as well if you would like to see these in the sidebar.


!!! Tiddler info button
<$vars tv-config-toolbar-class="tc-btn-invisible" tv-config-toolbar-text="no">
If you activate the info button {{$:/core/ui/Buttons/info}} in either the top or header or in the footer or bottom toolbar, then a matching tiddler info panel will be activated with it. (It is recommended to have only one info button active in only one of the toolbars.) 
</$vars>

If you rarely use this button and would like to keep it in the more menu, then you should place the tiddler info panel manually either in the header or in the footer part. To do so you can edit $:/plugins/telmiger/Tix/ViewTemplate/info and add one of these tags:

* $:/tags/TiddlerHeader if you want to use it at the top
* $:/tags/TiddlerFooter if you want to use it at the bottom

If necessary, you can then click the tag (see above) and drag the the .../info tiddler to the end of the list.",
    "title": "$:/plugins/telmiger/Tix/readme",
    "modified": "20220321231302898",
    "tags": "",
    "type": "text/vnd.tiddlywiki",
    "modifier": "Thomas Elmiger"
},

